Ask HN: Domain Lost – GitHub Email No Access
text:
I created this throwaway because I am ashamed of my stupidity. But also because i don't want people to know, which account to try to get in.

But here it is: I have been in a bad phase in my life. I was financially ruined and didn't see that my domains were cancelled. So I missed the grace period. Someone else got ahold of the domains (unused, cant find out how to contact the person).

I need access to my github account linked to that domain. I have important repos there. But after logging in, github sent a confirmation mail to the mail address i cant access anymore.

I hope the person is no dev. Also I really hope there is no catchall mail for that domain...

I need ideas on what to do now. Github does not seem to have any contact mail that would be helpful to me. And even if, I guess, they would not remove that email by a strangers request.

But I could prove i was the owner of the domain for many years - also when the github account was created with that mail address...

Any ideas?

title: Show HN: Dslcad a programming language and interpreter for building 3D models
text:
Hey HN. Over the last half a year I have been working on a 3D CAD programming language called DSLCAD. Today I am here to show my first release!

It is heavily inspired by OpenSCAD which got me hooked on the idea of a CAD programming language and what it can do.

Please let me know what you think. Ill be in the thread to answer any questions you may have.

Show HN: Spaghettify – A VSCode Extension to make your code worse with AI
text:
Recently, I saw Github Next Code Brushes (https://githubnext.com/projects/code-brushes) which is a VSCode extension that can use AI to do things like make your code more readable, add types, etc.

This inspired me: what if there was an extension that could use AI to make your code worse as well?

Meet Spaghettify. An extension I developed that can do things like:

- Obscure your code

- Introduce a bug

- Make the variable names way too descriptive

- Use nonsymmetrical whitespace

- Add irrelevant/rambling comments

- Document the code with emoji

- Document the code in any style (Dirty Limerick, Fast Talkin' 1930s Gangster)

I built this extension over the last couple of days and released it in collaboration with BCAD.one. It's available on the VSCode Marketplace, you will need an OpenAI API Key to use it. You can grab it here:

(https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=BCAD.spa...)

Ask HN: Whatever Happened to Udacity?
text: Udacity is an education company which, according to Wikipedia, is even a year older than Coursera or EdX. Its golden years seem to be around 2014-2015, when it produced a lot of great content, including courses by developers from Google (I particularly remember a PWA course released around 2015, and a course on web accessibility; a course on computer graphics was great as well), or professors from Georgia Tech. Then it all seemed to stop. Udacity still exists as a company; but it hasn't released any more exciting free courses since then. What happened? Both in 2015, when it looked like top educators were happy to partner with it and create content for it; and afterwards, when it all stopped? Does anyone here know their story?
